OL,7,F"My little boy has a condition which
OL,8,Fmeans if he has an episode we've got
OL,9,Fto get him to A&E really quickly and I
OL,10,Fhad no way of getting there. That was
OL,11,Fthe mental trauma for me.
OL,13,F"I'm definitely more cautious. I was
OL,14,Fcautious before, my car was locked, it
OL,15,Fwas virtually outside my house with a
OL,16,Fhundred other cars, you don't think
OL,17,Fyou have to do any more than that."
OL,19,FBridie eventually had to take out a
OL,20,Fsmall loan to buy a new car, and went
OL,21,Fsix weeks without a vehicle.
